            <!-- Section: Advanced Topics -->
            <section id="advanced" class="guide-section">
              <h2 class="guide-section__title">Advanced Topics</h2>

              <p class="guide-section__lead">
                Deep-dive topics for power users building complex integrations.
              </p>

              <h3>Custom Tool Development</h3>
              <p>
                Extend LichtFeld Studio's MCP capabilities by registering custom tools through the
                <a href={base + "docs/"} class="guide-link">Python plugin system</a>. Custom tools
                appear in the MCP manifest and can be invoked by any MCP client.
              </p>

              <div class="gs-code-block">
                <pre><code># In your LichtFeld Studio plugin
from lichtfeld import mcp

@mcp.tool("custom/analyze_normals")
def analyze_normals(threshold: float = 0.5):
    """Analyze surface normals and return statistics."""
    scene = get_active_scene()
    normals = scene.get_normals()

    outliers = np.sum(np.abs(normals) &lt; threshold)
    return {
        "total": len(normals),
        "outliers": int(outliers),
        "quality_score": 1.0 - (outliers / len(normals))
    }</code></pre>
                <button class="gs-code-block__copy" aria-label="Copy to clipboard">
                  <i class="bi bi-clipboard" aria-hidden="true"></i>
                </button>
              </div>

              <h3>Batch Operations</h3>
              <p>
                For high-throughput scenarios, use the batch endpoint to execute multiple tools
                in a single request:
              </p>
              <div class="gs-code-block">
                <pre><code>POST /mcp/batch
{
  "operations": [
    {"tool": "camera/set_position", "params": {"position": [0, 2, 5]}},
    {"tool": "render/capture_frame", "params": {"path": "./frame_001.png"}},
    {"tool": "camera/set_position", "params": {"position": [1, 2, 5]}},
    {"tool": "render/capture_frame", "params": {"path": "./frame_002.png"}}
  ]
}</code></pre>
                <button class="gs-code-block__copy" aria-label="Copy to clipboard">
                  <i class="bi bi-clipboard" aria-hidden="true"></i>
                </button>
              </div>

              <h3>WebSocket Alternative</h3>
              <p>
                For bidirectional communication, connect to the WebSocket endpoint at
                <code>ws://localhost:8080/mcp/ws</code>. This enables pushing commands from
                the server to clients and is ideal for collaborative editing scenarios.
              </p>

              <h3>Performance Optimization</h3>
              <ul class="guide-list">
                <li>
                  <strong>Use SSE for monitoring:</strong> Polling consumes more resources than
                  Server-Sent Events for real-time updates.
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Batch small operations:</strong> Group multiple tool calls using the batch endpoint.
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Cache resource reads:</strong> Scene info changes infrequently—cache locally
                  and invalidate on explicit updates.
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Async camera animations:</strong> Use the animate tool instead of
                  sequential set_position calls for smoother motion.
                </li>
              </ul>

              <h3>Security Considerations</h3>
              <div class="gs-callout gs-callout--warning">
                <span class="gs-callout__icon" aria-hidden="true">
                  <i class="bi bi-shield-exclamation"></i>
                </span>
                <div class="gs-callout__content">
                  <strong>Local Development Only</strong>
                  <p>
                    The MCP server is designed for local development and automation. Do not expose
                    port 8080 to external networks. For remote access, use SSH tunneling or a secure proxy.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </section>

